A. Clayton Perfall CPA: Executive Profile & Biography - Bloomberg









































  





















































































July 24, 2017 1:25 AM ET
Capital Markets

Company Overview of Union Street Acquisition Corp.



SnapshotPeople 




OverviewBoard MembersCommittees



Executive Profile
A. Clayton Perfall CPAExecutive Chairman, Chief Executive Officer and President, Union Street Acquisition Corp.AgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 5 Board Members in 5 different organizations across 5 different industries.See Board Relationships58--
Background

		Mr. A. Clayton Perfall, also known as Clay, CPA serves as an Executive Chairman, Chief Executive Officer and President of Union Street Acquisition Corp. He serves as the President of American Spirit Mailing. He serves as Operating Executive and Diversified Chairman at Tailwind Capital Group, LLC. Mr. Perfall served as the Chief Executive Officer of Archway Marketing Services, Inc., since 2008. He served as Chief Executive Officer of AHL Services, Inc. from September ... 2001 to 2008. From December 2000 to September 2001, He served as Chief Executive Officer of Convergence Holdings LLC. He served as the Chief Financial Officer of Snyder Communications Inc., from September 1996 to November 2000. He served as a Member of Senior Management Team of Snyder Communications, Inc. He served as Chief Financial Officer of Circle.com Inc. since September 1996. He spent 15 years at Arthur Andersen LLP, where he began his career, and served as its Partner. He had a wide range of responsibilities within the Washington, D.C., Baltimore, Maryland and Richmond, Virginia marketplaces, including responsibility for its Structured Finance and Financial Products tax practice and Business Valuation Services Group. He was a key participant in the development of Arthur Andersen's business strategies, the hiring of its professional staff and the development and marketing of its services. He serves as the Chairman of the Board of Directors of Diversified and Premier Store Fixtures. He has been an Independent Director of Colfax Corporation since September 21, 2010 and Comstock Holding Companies, Inc., since December 2004. He serves as a Director of Educational Direct. He serves as a Trustee of Mason School of Business at College of William & Mary. He serves as a Director of Counsel Corporation. He served as a Director of Circle.com Inc., since September 1996, AHL Services, Inc. from October 2001 to 2008 and Snyder Communications Inc. from September 1996 to November 2000. He served as a Chair of the Board of Governor of St. Stephen's & St. Agnes School for five years. He served as a Director of Imagitas. He served as a Director of inVentiv Health Inc. since September 1999. He holds a B.B.A in Accounting from the College of William & Mary.Read Full Background




